- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper explores different methods of solving the time-respecting subgraph isomorphism problem. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper discusses the implementation of different algorithms for solving the problem. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper deals with analyzing processes in network data sets. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possibility as the paper deals with communication networks.
